      "content": "but that's the thing... it doesn't feel like a storm. storms pass. this just feels like the end of the story. the artist is dead, and all that's left is the corpse of a person who doesn't even know how to be human without that creation. if the soul of the work is gone, then what is the point of maintaining the physical vessel? it's just a heavy, empty weight to carry around every single day.",
